The Chronicle Nqobile Tshili, Chronicle Reporter GOVERNMENT has deferred the opening of schools due to the spike in Covid-19 cases and threats posed by downgraded tropical depression Chalane. Schools initially scheduled to open on Monday January 4 for the First Term of 2021 and closing on March 24. In a statement on Wednesday afternoon, Primary and Secondary Education Permanent Secretary Mrs Tumisang Thabela said schools will not open but Ordinary and Advanced Level candidates will resume their final year examinations. More to followâ€¦